    "narrative": "The optimal path for Ghost Ride the WHIP today is led by our outfield heavy hitters against exploitable arms. **James Wood** (78.42) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) represent the strongest plays on the board, both benefitting from favorable matchups against starters with xERAs above 5.00. **Mickey Moniak** specifically stands out; while the park factor in his favor is significant, his ability to capitalize on the opposing pitcher's slow delivery\u2014an extra 2% boost to his already elite sprint-focused valuation\u2014solidifies his must-start status. Meanwhile, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (71.51) earns a high-tier nod in the UTIL spot, as favorable wind conditions and a strong platoon split against the right-handed starter elevate his efficiency score well above his baseline projection.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was undoubtedly **Kyle Karros** (62.71). Despite a score that would have qualified him for a start in most other contexts, the depth of our middle infield and the relative strength of our outfield options forced his exclusion. The optimizer leaned heavily toward **Brice Turang** and **Jose Caballero** due to their lead-off and bottom-of-order situational impacts, respectively, as well as the need to prioritize pure stolen base upside. Risks for the day remain centered on the bottom of our lineup, particularly **Dalton Rushing** and **Alex Freeland**, whose scores are contingent on pending lineup confirmations. While **Dalton Rushing** maintains a solid 59.88, the uncertainty regarding his spot in the order warrants close monitoring, especially as we balance the aggressive game-cap management inherent in our long-term Roto strategy.",
